node.text:
What an extremely informative chat regarding mindfulness and anxiety.
Speaking with professor/scientist and author @drshaunashapiro and Therapist @kimberleyquinlan we speak about the definition of mindfulness, how to approach mindfulness with compassion, how best to practice mindfulness and the scientific evidence behind mindfulness for anxiety

node.text: Dean speaks with @doc_amen about the impacts of pressure and fame on our mental health. How important it is to prioritise your mental health and how proud we all are of the steps @simonebiles has taken to put her mental health first.

node.text: The language we use and the words we choose matter in the words of @alifecoloredamber don’t be a a$$hole choose wisely ❤️❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 15, 2021 tagging @alifecoloredamber. May be an image of text that says 'WHY WE NO LONGER SAY "COMMIT SUICIDE" alifecoloredamber'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'People commit ㅇ Fraud Infidelity Murder Murder You get the point People do not commit Suicide O Anxiety Depression Mental Illness. alifecoloredamber'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'The term "commit suicide" was presented in the 20th century when it was considered a criminal act in many places in the world. **((It has now been decriminalized in many places (though not all), yet we still use this language)) Furthering this, suicide and and ideation is considered a serious sin in certain religions. alifecoloredamber'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'The day we quit viewing suicide as a moral failing to be "committed" and shift owad an approach of mental illness and sensitivity, is the day that we will begin to save more lives. alifecoloredamber'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'INSTEAD OF TRY "Committed Suicide" "Successful Suicide" "Died by Suicide" "Completed Suicide" or "Death by Suicide" "Failed Suicide Attempt" "Non-fatal Suicide Attempt" alifecoloredamber'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'DON'T BE AN ASSHOLE... A quick note that correcting another's language in a pompous or condescending manner is never very effective. Even more importantly do not correct the language of someone who is grieving or experiencing emotional distress! Focus on how you can be there for them and provide resources. alifecoloredamber'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'IG is not therapy! Everything shared on here is to be looked at as more of a guide, and not an intervention. Every person is different, and different tools or insight may resonate differently depending on your situation. Take care of your mental health. XOXo Amber alifecoloredamber'.
Photo shared by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 15, 2021 tagging @kimberleyquinlan, and @dlcanxiety. May be an image of text that says 'Types of Compulsions CBTschool.com @kimberleyquinlan'.
Photo shared by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 15, 2021 tagging @kimberleyquinlan, and @dlcanxiety. May be an image of text that says 'Types of Compulsions CBTschool.com @kimberleyquinlan'.
Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Compulsions can be physical or mental. CBTschool.com @kimberleyquinlan'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Compulsions are anything that is done to immediately remove the anxiety, doubt, physical discomfort, or uncertainty that comes from obsessions. CBTschool.com @kimberleyquinlan'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Physical compulsions might include: doing something a specific number of times (washing your hands, taking a sip of water), picking at your skin, doing things "just right" (stacking the dishes, folding the laundry CBTschool.com @kimberleyquinlan'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Avoidant Compulsions might include: Avoiding any person, object, substance, thought, or or place that triggers the obsession CBTschool.com @kimberleyquinlan'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Mental compulsions might include: rumination, mental "reviewing" of past events, checking (your attraction level, how your body feels, what emotions you are feeling) CBTschool.com @kimberleyquinlan'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Reassurance compulsions include: Googling asking loved ones questions, frequently visiting doctors or professionals related to your obsession, etc. CBTschool.com @kimberleyquinlan'.
